# Architecture Overview

PassReady is a predictive compliance intelligence engine.

## Target stack (Phase 5)

- **Frontend (Dashboard):** React + Tailwind CSS. Mobile-first, insights-first command center.
- **Backend (API):** Node.js + Express. Central orchestration logic.
- **Database:** PostgreSQL + Prisma. Single source of truth.
- **AI/Intelligence:** OpenAI API. Drafting, reply intelligence, risk scoring.
- **Workflow:** Delta-sync only — query FSA changes via `LastUpdatedDate`, not full re-scrapes.

## Core principles

- Modularize components: small, reusable UI pieces.
- Data-driven: reference `schema.prisma` before changing database logic.
- Robustness: every automated process (scraping, outreach, scoring) needs error handling and logging.

## This repo today (`passreadyfinder`)

Do **not** assume Phase 5 stack is already in place. Current implementation:

| Layer | Current |
|-------|---------|
| UI | Static HTML + Tailwind CDN (`public/control.html`, `public/review.html`) |
| API | Express (`src/server/createApp.ts`) |
| DB | Turso / libSQL (`src/engine/store/`), no Prisma |
| AI | Gemini via OpenAI-compatible API (`src/engine/drafter.ts`) |
| Find | Full FSA pagination per run (`src/engine/finder/fsa-finder.ts`), not delta-sync yet |

When editing this repo: follow **CONSTITUTION.md** / **PHASE2.md**, keep engine modules intact, and only introduce React/Prisma/delta-sync when explicitly requested as a migration task.
